| System task | Meaning               | Simulation effect                      |
| ----------- | --------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `$finish`   | Ends the simulation        | Stops simulation normally            |
| `$stop`     | Pauses simulation          | Simulator enters interactive mode    |
| `$exit`     | Exits from a program block | Terminates current program           |
| `$fatal`    | Reports fatal error        | Stops simulation immediately         |
| `$error`    | Reports an error           | Continues simulation but marks error |
| `$warning`  | Reports warning            | Continues simulation                 |
| `$info`     | Prints information message | Continues simulation                 |
| System Task   | Meaning                                       | Usage                         |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| `$display`    | Prints message once                           | Prints and adds newline       |
| `$write`      | Prints message                                | No automatic newline          |
| `$strobe`     | Prints at end of current simulation time step | Shows final updated values    |
| `$monitor`    | Continuously monitors signals                 | Prints whenever value changes |
| `$monitoron`  | Enables monitoring                            | Starts `$monitor`             |
| `$monitoroff` | Disables monitoring                           | Stops `$monitor`              |

| System Task | Meaning                        |
| ----------- | ------------------------------ |
| `$fopen`    | Opens a file                   |
| `$fclose`   | Closes a file                  |
| `$fdisplay` | Writes formatted data to file  |
| `$fwrite`   | Writes without newline to file |
| `$fstrobe`  | Writes at end of timestep      |
| `$fmonitor` | Monitors signals into file     |
| `$fflush`   | Flushes file buffer            |
| `$fscanf`   | Reads formatted data from file |
| `$fgets`    | Reads a line from file         |
| `$fgetc`    | Reads a character              |

| System Task  | Meaning               |
